sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a goods receipt document in SAP S/4HANA - RFC.

Inputs :

  • Connection Alias - Connection alias for the SAP S/4HANA – RFC spoke.
  • Select BAPI - Option to select either standard or custom BAPI.
  • Transaction Code for Goods Movement - Sample Input : 01 - Unique code to perform movement of materials.
  • Material Document Header - Complex object containing these fields:
    • Posting Date - Sample Input : 20220911
    • Document Date - Sample Input : 20220911
    • Reference Document Number
    • Number of Bill of Lading at Time of Goods Receipt
    • Goods Receipt/Issue Slip
    • User Name
    • Document Header Text
    • Print Version
    • Updated Information in Related User Data Field
    • Control Posting for External WMS
    • Reference Document Number (for Dependencies See Long Text)
    • Bill of Lading Number in GR (Dependencies: See Long Text)
    • Bar Code
  • Material Document Items - List of objects containing these fields:
    • Movement Type - Sample Input : 101
    • Quantity in Unit of Entry - Sample Input : 10
    • Purchase Order - Sample Input : 4500020425
    • Item - Sample Input : 00010
    • Movement Indicator - Sample Input : B
    • Storage Location
    • Material
    • Plant
    • Vendor
  • Additional Fields - Additional fields or values you want to add to the details. These fields are retrieved dynamically from SAP S/4HANA - RFC.

Outputs :

  • Goods Receipt - Goods receipt document details.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in SAP S/4HANA - RFC, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error as returned from SAP S/4HANA - RFC in the RETURN object. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

 

To use this action, the corresponding SAP S/4HANA - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP_S4HANA_RFC connection & credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
